SIMPLE: increscent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Increscent
<hw>In*cres"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>increscens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>increscere</ets>. See <er>Increase</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Increasing; growing; augmenting; swelling;
enlarging.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Between the <qex>incresent</qex> and decrescent moon.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Increasing; on the increase; --
said of the moon represented as the new moon, with the points turned
toward the dexter side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Increst</ent>⟦br⟧
